01:53:40,439 --> 01:53:42,282
Do you copy?

984
01:53:44,151 --> 01:53:46,825
Lois! Are you all right?

985
01:53:47,237 --> 01:53:50,616
Yeah. What happened?

986
01:53:51,742 --> 01:53:54,370
- Superman.
- Where is he?

987
01:53:55,871 --> 01:53:57,123
He went back.

988
01:53:59,750 --> 01:54:01,969
- Richard, we have to turn around.
- What? No.

989
01:54:02,127 --> 01:54:04,755
- We have to turn around!
- We barely made it out of there.

990
01:54:04,921 --> 01:54:07,515
- Now you want me to go back?
- Yes, please!

991
01:54:08,258 --> 01:54:10,101
He'll die.

992
01:54:13,096 --> 01:54:14,973
All right, hold on.

993
01:54:22,981 --> 01:54:25,109
[GROANING]

994
01:54:32,491 --> 01:54:34,334
Mom.

995
01:54:39,456 --> 01:54:41,424
You're asking yourself, "How?"

996
01:54:43,210 --> 01:54:48,182
Didn't your dad ever teach you
to look before you leap?

997
01:54:52,219 --> 01:54:55,189
Crystals. They're amazing, aren't they?

998
01:54:55,347 --> 01:54:58,601
They inherit the traits
of the minerals around them...

999
01:54:58,767 --> 01:55:03,568
kind of like a son
inheriting the traits of his father!

1000
01:55:06,358 --> 01:55:11,364
You took away five years of my life,
I'm just returning the favor!

1001
01:55:12,989 --> 01:55:14,286
[MUFFLED] Ah!

1002
01:55:14,866 --> 01:55:17,915
I'm still Superman!

1003
01:55:26,545 --> 01:55:29,970
Get up! Come on!

1004
01:55:38,390 --> 01:55:40,108
[WHIMPERING]

1005
01:56:07,210 --> 01:56:08,837
[SOBBING]

1006
01:56:52,547 --> 01:56:53,924
Ah!

1007
01:57:02,015 --> 01:57:04,017
Now, fly.

1008
01:57:19,324 --> 01:57:20,621
[WHEEZING]

1009
01:57:28,083 --> 01:57:29,255
[COUGHS]

1010
01:58:05,120 --> 01:58:08,090
So long, Superman.

1011
01:58:10,542 --> 01:58:13,637
<i>"JOR-EL".
Your leadership can stir others...</i>

1012
01:58:13,795 --> 01:58:15,968
<i>to their own capacities
for moral betterment.</i>

1013
01:58:16,131 --> 01:58:19,101
<i>The human heart is still subject
to monstrous deceits.</i>

1014
01:58:22,721 --> 01:58:25,600
<i>Our destruction could have been avoided.
At this very moment...</i>

1015
01:58:25,765 --> 01:58:27,392
<i>I could embrace you in my arms.</i>

1016
01:58:27,559 --> 01:58:29,982
<i>Your help would be called for endlessly.
Remember me.</i>

1017
01:58:30,145 --> 01:58:33,490
<i>Even for those tasks which human beings
could solve themselves.</i>

1018
01:58:43,908 --> 01:58:46,752
<i>Remember me, Kal-El.</i>

1019
01:58:46,911 --> 01:58:48,834
<i>Remember me.</i>

1020
01:58:50,624 --> 01:58:52,001
